"state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 9, "created_at": "2017-09-06T08:11:23Z", "updated_at": "2017-10-08T06:17:01Z", "closed_at": "2017-10-08T06:17:01Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "As noted in #1630 the metadata parser setup is no longer optimal for what we need to do.\r\n\r\nHere are a few thoughts on how it should change:\r\n\r\nParsers should have three major modes of operation:\r\n- report dataset-global metadata (this is what they do now)\r\n- report metadata for a given list of dataset components (files/directories)\r\n- dump all relevant metadata in a format that is optimal for query\r\n   - this mode is needed for aggregation\r\n   - homogenizing file metadata during aggregation is undesirable, as we would have to \"expand\" any metadata in a per-file format and possibly inflate it dramatically\r\n   - instead I propose to let each parser chose an optimal dump format that only itself needs to be able to understand. this dump is than put into a metadata object (see #1630) and used to perform file-based queries on aggregated metadata, when needed\r\n- consequently parser should be able to operate on an existing dataset, or on a set of metadata object files, and be able to perform the same operations", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_ur